19/10/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- The opposition candidate for mayor of Tirana, Spartak Ngjela, went to the prosecutor's office on Friday (17 October) seeking criminal charges related to irregularities stemming from last weekend's local elections. Ngjela accused Central Electoral Commission Chairman Ilirjan Celibashi and Local Government and Decentralisation Minister Ben Blushi of manipulating the election process and rigging voter lists and results. (BBC Monitoring, Albanian TV - 17/10/03)
